---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'April 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms — Mirage"
  description="Terms of use for the Mirage website."
  canonical="https://mirageinteractive.uk/terms"
>
  <main id="main" class="container-page py-20">
    <a href="/" class="text-sm text-ink-400 hover:text-white">&larr; Home</a>
    <h1 class="mt-6 font-display text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl">Terms of use</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-400">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-2xl space-y-6 text-ink-200">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white">This website</h2>
      <p>This website provides information about Mirage and the products we build. It does not constitute an offer, a warranty, or legal advice. Content may change without notice.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>The Mirage name, logo, and product names are trademarks of Mirage Interactive Ltd. The source of this website (HTML, CSS, images) is copyright Mirage Interactive Ltd unless explicitly licensed otherwise. Product-specific licensing is listed on each product's site.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Third-party attribution</h2>
      <p>We build on open-source software and credit contributors where due. Product attribution pages live inside each product.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Governing law</h2>
      <p>These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:legal@mirageinteractive.uk" class="text-mi-200 hover:text-white">legal@mirageinteractive.uk</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
